<p>Importantly, in June, there is a step change in international thinking on business and human rights. The UNâ€™s Human Rights Council unanimously approve the Guiding Principles for Business and Human Rights, the <a href="http://www.ohchr.org/Documents/Publications/GuidingPrinciplesBusinessHR_EN.pdf">UNGPs</a>.</p>

<p>The UNGP framework is the first corporate human rights responsibility initiative to be endorsed by the UN. It establishes a common global standard for preventing and addressing adverse human rights impacts of business activity. It also puts forward an approach based on due diligence.</p>
